%I A397190 #8 Jun 27 2026 23:36:30
%S A397190 1,3,2,28,239,22879,1312079
%N A397190 Number of directed Hamiltonian cycles in the mod n square grid graph, reduced for symmetry (with rotations, reflections, and translations not counted as distinct).
%C A397190 Here a "mod n square grid graph" is a n X n graph with wrapping allowed, e.g., a path can make a 1 unit step between the left and the right edge (same row) or the top and the bottom edge (same column) of the graph.
%H A397190 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/TorusGridGraph.html">Torus Grid Graph</a>.
%e A397190 a(4) = 28: equals A396483(4) (undirected) plus nonsymmetric cases counting 2 each instead of 1.
%Y A397190 Cf. A397017 (including non-Hamiltonian), A396483 (undirected), A397189 (directed Hamiltonian paths), A143246 (wrapping disallowed, not reduced).
%K A397190 nonn,walk,hard,more
%O A397190 1,2
